==English==
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun-reg}}

#{{chemistry}} Any [[binary compound]] of [[carbon]] and a more [[electropositive]] [[element]]
#{{chemistry}} The [[polyatomic]] ion C<sub>2</sub><sup>2&minus;</sup>, or any of its [[salt]]s.
#{{chemistry}} The [[monatomic]] ion C<sup>4&minus;</sup>, or any of its salts.
#{{chemistry}} A [[carbon]]-containing [[alloy]] or [[doping]] of a metal or [[semiconductor]], such as [[steel]].
#{{chemistry}} [[tungsten carbide|Tungsten carbide]].
# {{cycling}} [[trivial]] name for [[calcium carbide]] (CaC<sub>2</sub>), used to produce [[acetylene]] in bicycle lamps in the early 1900s.

